AGI - A delegation of Hamas will go on Monday, April 29 in Cairo for talks on the ceasefire in Gaza. A Hamas official said this to the AFP agency, adding that the delegation will give an answer to the proposal for ceasefire offered by the mediators and Israel. "A delegation of Hamas led by Khalil al-Hayya (a negotiator of the Islamist group and 'number 2' of the leader of Hamas in the Gaza Strip Yahya Sinwar) will arrive in Egypt and give the response of the movement" to the Israeli proposal during a meeting with Egyptian intelligence officials, said the official. The same news has also been reported by the Saudi daily Al-Sharq, according to which the new proposal contains "progress on the issue of the return of the displaced and on the number and categories of Palestinian prisoners who will be released in exchange for kidnapped". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
No doubt, however, that the next few hours will be decisive, being imminent the Israeli military operation in Rafah. The Chief of Staff of the IDF Herzi Halevi approved plans for the invasion. The Israeli media report it. The responsibility of the central corridor of the Gaza Strip was entrusted this week to the fighting teams reservists of the Yiftach and Carmeli Brigades, added the IDF, adding that the brigades are "executing targeted raids to eliminate terrorists and locate and destroy terrorist infrastructure in the area". "The raids are carried out by protecting the corridor at the centre of the Gaza Strip and carrying out actions that will allow the transfer of humanitarian aid," continued the IDF. The army also reported that the leader of the southern command and the commander of the 99th division, on Friday, carried out an assessment of the situation on the field, stating that new operational plans for the continuation of the fights were approved. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
President of the Palestinian National Authority Abu Mazen said - at a special meeting of the World Economic Forum in Riyadh - that "Israel will enter Rafah in the next few days", admitting to be concerned that "will try to remove the Palestinians from the West Bank after he has done so with the Gaza Strip. "The United States - he continued - is the only country that can prevent Israel from attacking Rafah. We call for the end of the fighting and the provision of aid to the Gaza Strip." "If Israel invades Rafah, it will cause the greatest catastrophe in the history of the Palestinian people. America is the only country that can prevent Israel from committing this crime," added the Palestinian President, who also said that a political solution is needed to unite the Gaza Strip, the West Bank and Jerusalem in an independent Palestinian state, a solution that must be implemented through the call of an international conference.
&nbsp;
Israel is obliged to destroy Hamas and bring the hostages home, "we are working on these two tasks and are determined to do both things," "it will take all the time necessary, but we have to complete this task." Israeli Defence Minister Yoav Gallant said this by speaking with soldiers on an Israeli military base. "I don't think there's an army in the world that can do what you do for these purposes and quality," he added.
&nbsp;
Meanwhile, the Hamas Ministry of Health announced a new budget of the victims provoked in the Gaza Strip, from the beginning of the war between Israel and the Palestinian Islamist movement, on October 7: the dead were 34.454 and 77.575 the wounded, in now more than 200 days of war.
